📌 Key Learning (Day 30)

This problem extends the Stock DP pattern by introducing a cooldown period after every sale.

The DP state remains:

dp[index][buy]

where:

index → Current day
buy → 1 if you can buy, 0 if you currently hold a stock

The key difference is in the sell transition:

Buy:
max(
-price + nextSell,
skip
)

Sell:
max(
price + dp[index+2][buy],
skip
)

After selling, you must skip the next day, so the next valid buying state starts at index + 2.
